        "sql": "SELECT o.order_id AS order_id, o.amount AS amount\nFROM orders o, (SELECT AVG(amount) AS avg_amount FROM orders) a\nWHERE o.amount > a.avg_amount\nORDER BY o.amount DESC, o.order_id;",
        "explanation": "1. The comma-join (an implicit `CROSS JOIN`) pairs every order with the one-row average table `a`.\n2. Now `a.avg_amount` is a plain column on each row, so the filter `o.amount > a.avg_amount` reads naturally.\n3. This is exactly the same threshold comparison as the scalar-subquery form and returns the identical rows (100, 55)."
