        "explanation": "1. The anti-join keeps a last-year customer only when **no** matching this-year row exists (`NOT EXISTS`).\n2. `SELECT DISTINCT` mimics the dedupe that `EXCEPT` does automatically, collapsing Bea's duplicate (though Bea is filtered out regardless).\n3. Identical result — Ada, Dev — confirming `EXCEPT` is the set-operator form of an anti-join."
