    "description": "The **symmetric difference** of two sets is everything in exactly one of them — `(A EXCEPT B) UNION (B EXCEPT A)`. It combines two set-difference operations with a final `UNION`, then a single `ORDER BY`.\n\n**Task:** two cafe locations each have a menu. Return the items that appear on **exactly one** menu (present at one location but not the other), tagging which side it came from.\n\nReturn columns **`item`**, **`only_at`**. Order by `item` ascending.",
    "setupSql": "CREATE TABLE downtown_menu (item TEXT);\nINSERT INTO downtown_menu (item) VALUES\n  ('Latte'), ('Mocha'), ('Scone'), ('Bagel'), ('Latte');\n\nCREATE TABLE uptown_menu (item TEXT);\nINSERT INTO uptown_menu (item) VALUES\n  ('Mocha'), ('Bagel'), ('Muffin'), ('Croissant');",
    "starterSql": "-- Items on exactly one of the two menus\nSELECT item, 'downtown' AS only_at FROM downtown_menu\nEXCEPT\nSELECT item, 'downtown' FROM uptown_menu  -- placeholder; fill the real symmetric difference\nORDER BY item;\n",
