        "explanation": "1. `GROUP BY region` collapses a region's three monthly rows into one group.\n2. Each `SUM(CASE WHEN month='Jan' THEN amount END)` keeps only that month's amount and sums it — the standard pivot that turns the `month` column into `jan`, `feb`, `mar` columns.\n3. The derived `total` is just `SUM(amount)` over the group, which equals `jan + feb + mar` because every row falls into exactly one of the three months.\n4. `ORDER BY region` gives a stable total order."
