    "description": "SQLite stores dates as TEXT, so to get a *number of days* between two dates you convert both to Julian day numbers with `julianday(x)` and subtract.\n\n**Task:** for each subscription return `id`, `signup`, `cancelled`, and `days_active` — the whole number of days between `signup` and `cancelled` (`cancelled - signup`). Both columns are plain `'YYYY-MM-DD'` dates, so the difference is already an integer; cast it to an integer with `CAST(... AS INTEGER)`. Order by `id`.\n\nOutput columns, in order: `id`, `signup`, `cancelled`, `days_active`.",
    "setupSql": "CREATE TABLE subscriptions (id INTEGER, signup TEXT, cancelled TEXT);\nINSERT INTO subscriptions (id, signup, cancelled) VALUES\n  (1, '2024-01-01', '2024-01-31'),\n  (2, '2024-02-10', '2024-03-01'),\n  (3, '2024-03-15', '2024-03-20'),\n  (4, '2024-04-01', '2024-06-15');",
