        "explanation": "1. `COALESCE(nickname, name, 'anonymous')` evaluates its arguments left to right and returns the first that is not NULL.\n2. For Alice and Carol, `nickname` is already non-NULL, so it is returned unchanged.\n3. For Bob and Dan, `nickname` is NULL, so COALESCE moves on and returns `name` (`'Bob'`, `'Dan'`).\n4. The final `'anonymous'` literal is a safety net that would only appear if both prior values were NULL. `ORDER BY id` keeps a stable order."
